jack2-pistomp (1.9.22-3) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Switch to sastraxi/jack2 fork at branch main. The fork carries all
    pi-stomp/JackBridge fixes on top of upstream v1.9.22 + the WAF backport
    from 1.9.23 (so Python 3.12 + Trixie waf work out of the box):
      - commit 3a2f2488: netadapter — clear PI controller integrator on
        ringbuffer reset (was the local pi-controller-reset quilt patch,
        now redundant).
      - commit 719d833a: netJACK2 — pin multicast group JOIN to a specific
        interface via JACK_NETJACK_MULTICAST_IF. Master-side fix for hosts
        with multiple routes to the multicast group, where
        IP_ADD_MEMBERSHIP + INADDR_ANY picks the wrong interface (en0
        wifi instead of en7 wired on the Mac).
      - commit b3bfc408: netadapter — pin multicast OUTGOING interface for
        the slave's sendto() to the same env var. Slave-side fix: hosts
        whose default route is on the wrong iface (wlan0 on the pi) but
        whose netJACK2 link is on a different one (eth0) need this so
        discovery packets leave on the cable, not wifi. Adds
        JackNetSocket::SetMulticastIF (IP_BOUND_IF on macOS, ip_mreqn
        imr_ifindex on Linux).
  * jackbridge-pi-up: drop the `-a ${JACKBRIDGE_MASTER:-169.254.125.10}`
    unicast-IP workaround; we now rely on the multicast pin above.
    Read /run/jackbridge.iface (set by jackbridge-pin-route's
    ExecStartPre=+ auto-detect) as the source of truth for the iface
    name, with $JACKBRIDGE_IFACE and finally eth0 as fallbacks. Avoids
    hardcoding eth0 on boards with multiple wired NICs.
  * Drop local patches now subsumed by the fork:
    - pi-controller-reset.patch (commit 3a2f2488).
    - waflib-imp-to-types.patch (the 1.9.23 WAF backport in the fork
      already wraps imp.new_module as types.ModuleType for Python 3.4+).

 -- pistomp <pistomp@example.com>  Sun, 28 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

jack2-pistomp (1.9.22-2) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Conflicts/Replaces/versioned-Provides libjack-jackd2-0 so Debian's stock
    libjackserver.so.0 is never installed alongside this build.
  * Install libraries to the arm64 multiarch dir (/usr/lib/aarch64-linux-gnu)
    so the patched libjackserver wins in ld.so.cache. Previously the package
    installed to /usr/lib (not on the linker search path); jackd loaded the
    stock Debian libjackserver instead of the patched one, causing
    jack.service to crash-loop and mod-host to hang at boot.

 -- pistomp <pistomp@example.com>  Tue, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

